In recent years, research has focussed on automatic speech recognition in meetings (Stolcke et al., 2004; Metze et al., 2004; Hain et al., 2005), activity recognition (Rybski and Veloso, 2004), automatic meeting summarization (Murray et al., 2005), meeting phase detection (Banerjee and Rudnicky, 2004) and topic detection (Galley et al., 2003).
